---
title: Shawarma-Rama Chicken Salad Sandwiches with Baby Lettuce Salad
description: Come one, come all to the amazing sandwich spectacle—the Shawarma-rama! Yes, it’s a nutritious, tasty, all-around satisfying dinner you’ll be happy you ordered! Step right up to this sando-rama of seared shawarma-spiced chicken combined with sweet lemon juice-plumped apricots and scallions in a creamy yogurt dressing. It’s topped with crisp lettuce, then tucked into a soft brioche bun and splashed with hot sauce to taste. Add a lightly dressed baby lettuce sideshow salad for a never-before-seen flavor-meets-texture extravaganza!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64b69d2858f85793eaa6dbf5-9c89b718.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64b69d2858f85793eaa6dbf5.pdf
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 750 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 70 g
  sugar: 24 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 740 mg
author: HelloFresh
time required: 25 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/shawarma-rama-chicken-salad-sandwiches-64b69d2858f85793eaa6dbf5
cuisine: Mediterranean
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @Lemon{1}. Thinly slice @Scallions{2}.

Trim and discard root end from @Baby Lettuce{1}; separate leaves.

Pat @Chicken Breast Strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all
over with @Shawarma Spice Blend{1%unit}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle
of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken
in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked
through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to cool.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @Dried Apricots{1%ounce}, juice
from half the lemon, and @Sugar{1/2%tsp}. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{};
microwave until apricots are slightly softened and plump, ~{30-35%seconds}.

Roughly chop chicken into bite-size pieces if necessary.

In a large #bowl{}, combine chicken, scallions, apricots and their liquid,
@Yogurt{4%tablespoon}, @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, a drizzle of
@Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}, a big pinch of salt, @pepper{}, and @Sugar{1/4%tsp}.
Taste and season with more salt and pepper if desired.

Halve @Brioche Buns{2} and toast until golden.

Top each bottom bun with a few lettuce leaves and chicken salad; drizzle
chicken salad with as much @Hot Sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like. Close
sandwiches.

Wipe out bowl used for chicken salad.

Roughly chop remaining lettuce leaves and place in same bowl. Add juice from
one lemon wedge and a large drizzle of olive oil; toss to combine. Season with
salt and pepper to taste.

Divide sandwiches and salad between #plates{}. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.